<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="205" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,769,905]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">
Widespread and common in tropical America, from 
<collectingCountry box="[783,872,807,833]" name="Panama" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Panama</collectingCountry>
so far known from 
<collectingRegion box="[1100,1193,806,832]" country="Panama" name="Chiriqui" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Chiriqui</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1251,1331,806,832]" country="Panama" name="Darien" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Darién</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gradstein, S. R." pageId="4" pageNumber="205" pagination="149 - 177" refId="ref22016" refString="Gradstein, S. R. (2013) Afro-American Hepatics revisited. Polish Botanical Journal 58 (1): 149 - 177. http: // www. ib-pan. krakow. pl / ibwyd / pol-b-j / pbj 58. htm" type="journal article" year="2013">Gradstein (2013)</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName authority="E. W. Jones" authorityName="E. W. Jones" box="[299,706,842,869]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Calypogeiaceae" genus="Calypogeia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="afrocaerulea">
<emphasis box="[299,577,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Calypogeia afrocaerulea</emphasis>
E.W. Jones
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[897,1042,843,869]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Calypogeiaceae" genus="Calypogeia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis box="[897,1042,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">C. peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, therefore 
<taxonomicName box="[1161,1307,843,869]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Calypogeiaceae" genus="Calypogeia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis box="[1161,1307,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">C. peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed now as an Afro-American species.
</paragraph>
